cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.CL

The paper discusses the use of neural networks for solving mathematical problems, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes a syntax for representing mathematical problems and methods for generating datasets, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. The use of neural networks for solving mathematical problems also falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
